-- Obamacare, Holiday Sales, Berlusconi, HP: Week Ahead Nov. 23-30
-- B y   H e a t h e r   L a n g a n ,   G r e g   M i l e s   a n d   J i m   M c D o n a l d
-- 2013-11-21T22:58:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-21/obamacare-holiday-sales-berlusconi-hp-week-ahead-nov-23-30.html
President  Barack Obama  has set a
Nov. 30 deadline to fix the administration’s health-care
website. The federal program’s rollout, including the site’s
technical problems, has hurt the president’s approval rating.  The U.S. holiday shopping season gets into full swing on
Black Friday, the day after Thanksgiving, when retailers
generate revenue gains by offering steep discounts. Consumers
account for about 70 percent of the economy.  U.S. pending home sales  and  housing starts  probably jumped,
data may show.  Italy’s Senate votes on a motion to expel former Prime
Minister Silvio Berlusconi, who was convicted of tax fraud.  The Swiss vote on whether to stop executives from earning
more than 12 times the compensation of the lowest-paid employee.  Hewlett-Packard Co. (HPQ)  and  Tiffany & Co. (TIF)  release results.  SATURDAY, NOV. 23  To contact the reporters on this story:
